<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-11-30T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-11-30T11:00:00-05:00" n="694" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d694">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/11–3051: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bruce</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-11-30T17:00:00+01:00">November
                                    30, 1951—5 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3240. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 3194, Nov 27 communicated
                            to <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> by note today. Only
                            immediate reaction was comment that French wld probably request
                            consultation.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>